===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|god}}, from {{inh|en|ang|god||deity}}, originally neuter, then changed to masculine to reflect the change in religion to Christianity, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*gudą}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*ǵʰutós||invoked (one)}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*ǵʰewH-||to call, to invoke}} or {{m|ine-pro|*ǵʰew-||to pour}}. Not related to the word {{m|en|good}}.

